	<section class="row gx-md-5 section-portfolio">
		<div class="col-xl-3 pr-5 section-portfolio-label">
			<i class="fa-regular fa-file-lines"></i>
			<h2 class="pr-5">Planning &amp; Wireframing</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="col-xl-9">
			<div class="row gx-md-5 mb-5">
				<div class="col-xl-6">
					<div class="card card-normal">
						<h3>Research &amp; Analysis</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Historical Analytics</li>
							<li>Competitive Analysis</li>
							<li>Industry best-practices (marketing focused)</li>
							<li>Interviews with stakeholders</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-xl-6">
					<div class="card card-normal">
						<h3>Brainstorming &amp; Wireframing</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>
								Internal "design jam" with senior designers and in-house
								creative team
							</li>
							<li>User journey mapping</li>
							<li>Determining best page flow for consumption</li>
							<li>Crafting component variations for certain use-cases</li>
							<li>Feedback from SEO and CRO for best-practices</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="row gx-md-5 section-portfolio">
		<div class="col-xl-3 pr-5 section-portfolio-label">
			<i class="fa-brands fa-figma"></i>
			<h2 class="pr-5">Design &amp; Prototyping</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="col-xl-9">
			<p class="mb-5">
				While the website redesign presented a substantial challenge, as a design lead, I had
				confidence in our execution and delivery capabilities. This assurance stemmed from our
				development of a design system that significantly streamlined our design process and
				approach. Moreover, consistently sharing ideas and progress updates with all creative
				stakeholders throughout the journey ensured alignment and mutual understanding.
			</p>
			<div class="row gx-md-5">
				<div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
					<a
						class="card card-portfolio card-padding card-link"
						data-bs-toggle="modal"
						data-bs-target="#galleryModal"
						data-bs-image="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-component-variations.png"
						data-bs-title="Automation Anywhere - Website Redesign">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-12">
								<h3>Component Variations</h3>
								<p>
									Common content blocks had pre-built variants to choose
									from, which allowed for presentation flexibility.
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-12 img">
								<img
									src="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-component-variations.png"
									class=""
									alt={title}
								/>
							</div>
						</div>
					</a>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
					<a
						class="card card-portfolio card-padding card-link"
						data-bs-toggle="modal"
						data-bs-target="#galleryModal"
						data-bs-image="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-navigation-updates.png"
						data-bs-title="Automation Anywhere - Website Redesign">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-12">
								<h3>Navigation Updates</h3>
								<p>
									Several rounds of navigation updates were executed, to
									cater to the new product stack and narrative.
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-12 img">
								<img
									src="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-navigation-updates.png"
									class=""
									alt={title}
								/>
							</div>
						</div>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row gx-md-5">
				<div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
					<a
						class="card card-portfolio card-padding card-link"
						data-bs-toggle="modal"
						data-bs-target="#galleryModal"
						data-bs-image="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-page-templatization.png"
						data-bs-title="Automation Anywhere - Website Redesign">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-12">
								<h3>Page Templatization</h3>
								<p>
									For faster page building and consistency, we templatized
									the most common sections. This allowed PMMs to more
									easily plan for the future.
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-12 img">
								<img
									src="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-page-templatization.png"
									class=""
									alt={title}
								/>
							</div>
						</div>
					</a>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6 mb-5">
					<a
						class="card card-portfolio card-padding card-link"
						data-bs-toggle="modal"
						data-bs-target="#galleryModal"
						data-bs-image="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-responsive-layouts.png"
						data-bs-title="Automation Anywhere - Website Redesign">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-12">
								<h3>Responsive Layouts</h3>
								<p>
									Most top-level layouts and MVP pages were built with
									responsive design frames. Aiding not only PMMs, but the
									development team as well.
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-12 img">
								<img
									src="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-responsive-layouts.png"
									class=""
									alt={title}
								/>
							</div>
						</div>
					</a>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-12 mb-5">
					<a
						class="card card-portfolio card-full card-link"
						data-bs-toggle="modal"
						data-bs-target="#galleryModal"
						data-bs-image="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-subdomain-support.png"
						data-bs-title="Automation Anywhere - Website Redesign">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-6">
								<h3>Subdomain Support</h3>
								<p>
									I took lead and made it a priority for our company's sub
									domain properties to adopt the new design system. My
									main role was to evangelize the system and provide any
									UI/UX support that was needed. I managed senior
									designers during the adoption.
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-6 img">
								<img
									src="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-subdomain-support.png"
									class=""
									alt={title}
								/>
							</div>
						</div>
					</a>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-12 mb-5">
					<a
						class="card card-portfolio card-full card-link"
						data-bs-toggle="modal"
						data-bs-target="#galleryModal"
						data-bs-image="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-cultural-design.png"
						data-bs-title="Automation Anywhere - Website Redesign">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-6">
								<h3>Region Specific, Cultural Design</h3>
								<p>
									I worked directly with regional managers to make sure
									our visual style was catering to the corresponding
									culture. Options were provided and iterations were made.
									I managed senior designers during these stages.
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-6 img">
								<img
									src="/images/work/aai-website/thumb-cultural-design.png"
									class=""
									alt={title}
								/>
							</div>
						</div>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="row gx-md-5 section-portfolio">
		<div class="col-xl-3 pr-5 section-portfolio-label">
			<i class="fa-solid fa-rotate"></i>
			<h2 class="pr-5">Feedback &amp; Iteration</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="col-xl-9">
			<div class="row gx-md-5 mb-5">
				<div class="col-xl-6">
					<div class="card card-normal">
						<h3>Feedback Gathering</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>
								As new content docs and requirements were rolling in, WCS team
								made sure to stay in sync with the strategy of "hot" pages
							</li>
							<li>
								Sub-domain owners and key development team members provided
								direct feedback on usage and areas of improvement for use
								cases
							</li>
							<li>
								Reporting back to the development team for updates to the
								design system, updates to sections or net new pages.
							</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-xl-6">
					<div class="card card-normal">
						<h3>Updates &amp; Evolution</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>
								New designs in the pipeline: Customer Stories, Blogs, Asset
								Library and Events & Webinars
							</li>
							<li>
								Continued experimentation with Conversion Rate methods and
								Call to Action approaches
							</li>
							<li>Continued monthly support for sub-domain redesign projects</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="row gx-md-5 section-portfolio mb-5">
		<div class="col-xl-3 col-12 pr-5 section-portfolio-label">
			<!-- <i class="fa"></i> -->
			<h2 class="pr-5">Next steps&hellip;</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="col-xl-4 col-6 pt-3">
			<p><a href="/portfolio">Back to Portfolio</a></p>
		</div>
		<div class="col-xl-5 col-6 pt-3 text-end">
			<p><a href="#">Back to Top</a></p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
